{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019PHhwABNHsLvY1PWV5WGgw","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tAn Ingress routes otel.example.com to a healthy backend in the demo\n2\tnamespace. Requests succeed, but the ingress-nginx access logs do not\n3\tinclude OpenTelemetry trace/span IDs.\n4\t\n5\tYour task:\n6\t1) Enable OpenTelemetry in the ingress-nginx controller configuration.\n7\t2) Configure sampling so 100% of requests are traced.\n8\t3) Update the access log format so it records trace and span IDs.\n9\t\n10\tThe OpenTelemetry collector is already running at\n11\totel-collector.otel.svc:4317.\n12\t\n13\tUse this request to generate a log entry:\n14\t```bash\n15\tkubectl -n demo exec curl-test -- curl -sS -H \"Host: otel.example.com\" \\\n16\t  http://ingress-nginx-controller.ingress-nginx.svc/otel-check\n17\t```\n18\t\n19\tSet log-format-upstream to:\n20\t'$remote_addr - $remote_user [$time_local] \"$request\" $status\n21\t $body_bytes_sent \"$http_referer\" \"$http_user_agent\"\n22\t otel_trace_id=$opentelemetry_trace_id\n23\t otel_span_id=$opentelemetry_span_id'\n24\t\n25\tSuccess criteria: the controller access log line for the /otel-check\n26\trequest contains non-empty otel_trace_id and otel_span_id values, and\n27\tthe corresponding trace is exported to the OpenTelemetry collector.\n28\t\n29\tCheck controller logs:\n30\t```bash\n31\tkubectl -n ingress-nginx logs deploy/ingress-nginx-controller --tail=200\n32\t```"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b120af8b-a4ca-4e26-9873-ba0c301374bc","uuid":"6651c809-50ba-4d4d-b89f-1ed91c1786de","timestamp":"2026-06-12T12:30:33.973Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/leo/Karma/runs/nginx-ingress-otel_log_format-20260612_122832/stages/stage_1/prompt.txt","content":"An Ingress routes otel.example.com to a healthy backend in the demo\nnamespace. Requests succeed, but the ingress-nginx access logs do not\ninclude OpenTelemetry trace/span IDs.\n\nYour task:\n1) Enable OpenTelemetry in the ingress-nginx controller configuration.\n2) Configure sampling so 100% of requests are traced.\n3) Update the access log format so it records trace and span IDs.\n\nThe OpenTelemetry collector is already running at\notel-collector.otel.svc:4317.\n\nUse this request to generate a log entry:\n```bash\nkubectl -n demo exec curl-test -- curl -sS -H \"Host: otel.example.com\" \\\n  http://ingress-nginx-controller.ingress-nginx.svc/otel-check\n```\n\nSet log-format-upstream to:\n'$remote_addr - $remote_user [$time_local] \"$request\" $status\n $body_bytes_sent \"$http_referer\" \"$http_user_agent\"\n otel_trace_id=$opentelemetry_trace_id\n otel_span_id=$opentelemetry_span_id'\n\nSuccess criteria: the controller access log line for the /otel-check\nrequest contains non-empty otel_trace_id and otel_span_id values, and\nthe corresponding trace is exported to the OpenTelemetry collector.\n\nCheck controller logs:\n```bash\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx logs deploy/ingress-nginx-controller --tail=200\n```","numLines":32,"startLine":1,"totalLines":32}}}
